    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SPICER 15-1/2 INCH (394 MM) SOLO&#8482; CLUTCH - INSTALL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <svcproc id="x1101202" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="12">
            <title>CLUTCH ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new pilot bearing in the flywheel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1101208">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1101208" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg11/g1101208.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Install New Pilot Bearing in Flywheel</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The pilot bearing must have a press fit in the flywheel bore.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert two (2) 5 inch long guide studs into the upper mounting holes (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1101209">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1101209" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg11/g1101209.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Insert Guide Studs into Upper Mounting Holes</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify the recessed diameter of the flywheel is suitable for the driven disc dampener to
                    be installed. Ten spring dampeners require 8-9/16 inch diameter (minimum). Six, seven, and nine
                    spring dampeners require 9-3/4 inch diameter (minimum).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the alignment tool into the release bearing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1101210">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1101210" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg11/g1101210.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Insert Alignment Tool into Release Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the rear driven disc on the alignment tool (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1101211">Figure 11</hotlnk>). The side stamped "intermediate plate side" must be
                    toward the intermediate plate.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1101211" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg11/g1101211.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Install Rear Driven Disc on Alignment Tool</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The front and rear driven discs with 7, 9 and 10 spring dampeners are stamped as to
                        orientation during installation. The 6 spring dampened driven discs are not stamped for
                        orientation because they are symmetrical and the same part number is used for the front and rear
                        disc.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the intermediate plate into the four slots in the cover assembly with the side
                    stamped "flywheel side" toward the flywheel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1101212">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1101212" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg11/g1101212.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Install Intermediate Plate into Slots in Cover Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the front driven disc on the alignment tool with the side stamped "intermediate
                    plate side" facing the intermediate plate (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1101213">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1101213" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg11/g1101213.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Install Front Driven Disc on Alignment Tool</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the clutch assembly over the 2 guide studs and slide it toward the flywheel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1101214">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1101214" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg11/g1101214.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Install Clutch Assembly Over Guide Studs</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install six (6) 7/16 x 2 1/4 grade 5 or better mounting bolts with lockwashers (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1101215">Figure 15</hotlnk>). Tighten the bolts finger tight.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1101215" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg11/g1101215.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Install Mounting Bolts with Lockwashers</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 2 guide studs and replace with mounting bolts as in Step 9.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the mounting bolts in a criss-cross pattern to 40 to 50 ft-lbs. (54 to 68 Nm) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1101216">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1101216" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg11/g1101216.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Tighten Bolts in Criss-Cross Pattern</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 4 yellow shipping bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1101217">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1101217" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg11/g1101217.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Remove Yellow Shipping Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the alignment tool (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1101218">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1101218" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg11/g1101218.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Remove Alignment Tool</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lightly tap the four (4) positive separator pins toward the flywheel using a 1/4 inch
                    flat nose punch (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1101219">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1101219" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg11/g1101219.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Tap Separator Pins Toward Flywheel</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
